w Pool\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1330}, {\"ngram\": \"our hands\", \"from\": 1334, \"to\": 1343}, {\"ngram\": \"these Olympics\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1361}]}, {\"sentence\": \")\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cMy objective was to break a record tonight,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Marchand said.\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1416, \"end\": 1424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9852987591724566, \"rank\": 0.014872137983238814, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \")\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cMy objective\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1380}, {\"ngram\": \"a record\", \"from\": 1394, \"to\": 1402}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI felt really good.\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1453, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1435}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the last [lap], I took advantage of the crowd because I knew I was ahead, I knew I was an Olympic champion.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d That narrow miss of the record he set last year hardly mattered at the end.\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1644, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"advantage\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1489}, {\"ngram\": \"the crowd\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic champion.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d That narrow miss\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1584}, {\"ngram\": \"the record\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1598}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1642}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marchand\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s gold-medal rout of silver medalist Tomoyuki Matsushita of Japan and bronze medalist Foster delivered on expectations that were set Eiffel Tower-high last year, when he first erased Phelps\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 400 IM world record.\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1702, \"end\": 1712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Panasonic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.273619204800841e-31, \"text\": \"Matsushita\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Panasonic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Panasonic\"}, {\"begin\": 1716, \"end\": 1721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9983060424363455, \"rank\": 0.0016968307319514195, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 1742, \"end\": 1748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myles_Birket_Foster\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.854362233546178e-15, \"text\": \"Foster\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myles_Birket_Foster\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myles_Birket_Foster\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Marchand\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s gold-medal rout\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1673}, {\"ngram\": \"expectations\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1774}, {\"ngram\": \"Phelps\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 400 IM world record\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 1868}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coached by Bob Bowman, the same man who mentored Phelps to a record 28 Olympic medals (23 of them gold), Marchand is now officially the biggest star of the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 2041, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1885, \"end\": 1891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"score\": 0.9988378088996701, \"rank\": 0.0011635433599816514, \"text\": \"Bowman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\"}, {\"begin\": 1919, \"end\": 1925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5390417822916936e-14, \"te