 measured them in the gliding position primarily on starts and turns\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094when they are streamlined and not actively moving their limbs.\", \"from\": 4609, \"to\": 4754, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Passive drag\", \"from\": 4609, \"to\": 4621}, {\"ngram\": \"the gliding position\", \"from\": 4639, \"to\": 4659}, {\"ngram\": \"starts\", \"from\": 4673, \"to\": 4679}, {\"ngram\": \"their limbs\", \"from\": 4742, \"to\": 4753}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Active drag measured them during actual swimming movements.\", \"from\": 4755, \"to\": 4814, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Active drag\", \"from\": 4755, \"to\": 4766}, {\"ngram\": \"actual swimming movements\", \"from\": 4788, \"to\": 4813}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marchand was elite in both categories.\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cHe\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s almost like natural selection,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Peterson says of his body type.\", \"from\": 4815, \"to\": 4931, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Marchand\", \"from\": 4815, \"to\": 4823}, {\"ngram\": \"both categories\", \"from\": 4837, \"to\": 4852}, {\"ngram\": \"natural selection\", \"from\": 4877, \"to\": 4894}, {\"ngram\": \"Peterson\", \"from\": 4899, \"to\": 4907}, {\"ngram\": \"his body type\", \"from\": 4916, \"to\": 4929}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Legs create more drag than torso because they don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t float, and Peterson says Marchand is blessed with a larger and longer torso and shorter legs\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094much like Michael Phelps.\", \"from\": 4932, \"to\": 5106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5011, \"end\": 5019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9852987591724566, \"rank\": 0.014872137983238814, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}, {\"begin\": 5091, \"end\": 5105, 